"title": "1170: God, unity of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1170: god, unity of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God acts as a unity in all his deeds. The three persons of the Trinity are united in one Godhead. They are interrelated with one another, share the same attributes and co-operate in the same work. God's characteristics are consistent, expressing his integral divine nature.</p>\n<h2>God is one</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:4\">DEU 6:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:29\">MRK 12:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:32\">MRK 12:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:4\">1CO 8:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:20\">GAL 3:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:5-Eph4:6\">EPH 4:5–4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:5\">1TI 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas2:19\">JAS 2:19</a></p>\n<h2>The three persons of the Trinity are united in one Godhead</h2>\n<h3>All three are interrelated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:9-Rom8:11\">ROM 8:9–8:11</a></strong> <em>The interchange between the persons of the Trinity reflects their unity in terms of activity.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:23\">JHN 14:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:14\">2CO 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:18\">EPH 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></p>\n<h3>The Son is one with the Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:30\">JHN 10:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:40\">MAT 10:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:37\">MRK 9:37</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:48\">LUK 9:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:16\">LUK 10:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:16\">JHN 8:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:9\">JHN 14:9</a></p>\n<h3>The Spirit is one with God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam23:2-2Sam23:3\">2SA 23:2–23:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:11\">PSA 51:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a></p>\n<h2>The three persons are one in character</h2>\n<h3>All three are eternal</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:26\">ROM 16:26</a> <em>the Father</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:6\">ISA 9:6</a> <em>the Son</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a> <em>the Spirit</em></p>\n<h3>All three are all-knowing</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:13-Isa40:14\">ISA 40:13–40:14</a> <em>the Father</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:24-John2:25\">JHN 2:24–2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John21:17\">JHN 21:17</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor2:10-1Cor2:11\">1CO 2:10–2:11</a> <em>the Spirit</em></p>\n<h3>All three are holy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a> <em>the Father</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:24\">MRK 1:24</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:14\">ACT 3:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:26\">JHN 14:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:4\">ROM 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>All three are called Lord and God</h3>\n<p>The Father:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:25\">MAT 11:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:22\">ACT 3:22</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:6\">1CO 8:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:1\">JHN 1:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:28\">JHN 20:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:36\">ACT 10:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:1\">2PE 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:3-Acts5:4\">ACT 5:3–5:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:17-2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:17–3:18</a></p>\n<h3>All three are glorious</h3>\n<p>The Father:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:2\">ACT 7:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17\">EPH 1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:14\">JHN 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:41\">JHN 12:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:8\">2CO 3:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet4:14\">1PE 4:14</a></p>\n<h2>The three persons share in the same work</h2>\n<h3>In creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen1:1-Gen1:3\">GEN 1:1–1:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:6\">PSA 33:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps104:30\">PSA 104:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:3-John1:4\">JHN 1:3–1:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>In Jesus Christ's ministry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:34\">JHN 3:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:38\">ACT 10:38</a></p>\n<h3>In salvation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:2\">1PE 1:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor1:21-2Cor1:22\">2CO 1:21–1:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:4-Titus3:6\">TIT 3:4–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>In indwelling the church</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:22\">EPH 2:22</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19\">1CO 6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:17\">EPH 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>In directing the church's mission</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:6-Acts16:10\">ACT 16:6–16:10</a></strong> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:27\">ACT 14:27</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:1\">GAL 1:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:18-Matt28:20\">MAT 28:18–28:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:7-Acts1:8\">ACT 1:7–1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:2\">ACT 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts13:4\">ACT 13:4</a></p>\n<h2>God's characteristics are consistent</h2>\n<h3>His love and justice are in unity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:6–34:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:14-2Sam7:15\">2SA 7:14–7:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:6-Ps103:8\">PSA 103:6–103:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:25-Rom3:26\">ROM 3:25–3:26</a></p>\n<h3>His wrath and mercy are in unity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel2:11-Joel2:13\">JOL 2:11–2:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:18\">JHN 3:16–3:18</a> <em>It is particularly in the cross of Jesus Christ that the perfect balance between God's wrath and justice and his love and mercy are seen</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:7-Rom2:8\">ROM 2:7–2:8</a></p>",
